  "notes": "Proof authority: Lean kernel via the tracked proof-search loop (episode 6f12df1e), kernel_verified on the first attempt. Completes the domain's 'inverse' focus pair alongside last cycle's `left_inverse_injective` -- this was the explicit backlog item that cycle left for exactly this pickup. `Function.RightInverse g f` unfolds to `Function.LeftInverse f g`, i.e. `∀ x, f (g x) = x`, so the witness `g b` with `h b : f (g b) = b` proves surjectivity directly, no rewriting needed (simpler than `left_inverse_injective`'s two-step congrArg/rw, hence D0 not D1).",
